The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Prisoner kills 1, injures 2
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Prisoner kills 1, injures 2
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	Patna, July 25: A prisoner was killed and two others were injured today in a clash between two jailbirds at Bihar Sharief divisional jail in Nalanda, 60km from here.        
	An undertrial prisoner, Arjun Singh, battered Alakhdeo Mahto (65), serving a life sentence, to death with a brick, prison officers said.         
	The officers said altercation over some trivial issue led to the shocking incident.         
	Officials rushed Mahto to Bihar Sharief Sadar hospital, where the doctors declared the prisoner brought dead.        
	Arjun also attacked Mohammand Arzoo and Rajnandan Mahto when the two tried to intervene.         
	Rajnandan Mahto, who received severe head injuries during the fight, has been admitted to the Patna Medical College Hospital (PMCH), where his condition is stated to be serious.                                                                                                                                                                         
